Centered columns are placed in the middle of the row. This does not center their content, but centers the grid element, itself. This is accomplished by adding a class of large-centered or small-centered depending on which breakpoint you want the columns to center on. Small versions will carry through all breakpoints if not overridden by a large version. You can center any number of columns you have. To have a column not carry it's small-centered to large, add a class of large-uncentered. Centered columns are placed in the middle of the row.
